Usage:
   /usr/bin/vfyserv  [-c ] [-o] [-p port] [-d dbdir] [-w password] [-f pwfile]
   		[-C cipher(s)]  [-l <url> -t <nickname> ] hostname
Where:
  -c            dump server cert chain into files
  -o            perform server cert OCSP check
  -p            server port to be used
  -d dbdir      use security databases in "dbdir"
  -w password   key database password
  -f pwfile     token password file
  -C cipher(s)  communication cipher list
  -l url        OCSP responder location. This location is used to
                check  status  of a server  certificate.  If  not 
                specified, location  will  be taken  from the AIA
                server certificate extension.
  -t nickname   OCSP Trusted Responder Cert nickname

